						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near a well in survey No. 230 by the side of the cart-track leading to Rāvulāpuram from Manēpallepādu.</p>						

						<p>11th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 11th century A.D. on palaeographical grounds.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift <hi rend="italic">(dharmmuvu)</hi> of land of 1 <hi rend="italic">kha</hi> in extent to the God Bhīmēśvara for the merit of Chōḍarāju.</p>						

						</summary>
